quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  43,85,"And Blessed be He to Whom belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, and all that is between them, and with Whom is the knowledge of the Hour, and to Whom you (all) will be returned."
  43,86,"And those whom they invoke instead of Him have no power of intercession - except for those who bear witness to the truth knowingly (i.e. believed in the Oneness of Allâh, and obeyed His Orders), and they know (the facts about the Oneness of Allâh).{1}",1:[{43:86} See the footnote of {2:165}.]
  43,87,"And if you ask them who created them, they will surely say: "
  50,10,"And tall date-palms, with ranged clusters."
  50,11,"A provision for (Allâh’s) slaves. And We give life therewith to a dead land. Thus will be the resurrection (of the dead)."
  50,12,"Denied before them (i.e. these pagans of Makkah) the people of Nûh (Noah), and the dwellers of Rass, and Thamûd;"
  51,4,"And those (angels) who distribute (provisions, rain, and other blessings) by (Allâh’s) Command."
  51,5,"Verily, that which you are promised (i.e. Resurrection in the Hereafter and receiving the reward or punishment of good or bad deeds) is surely true."
  51,6,"And verily, the Recompense is sure to happen."